    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-07-05T02:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-07-05T02:00:00-05:00" n="336"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d336">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 EW (Peace)/7–547: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Yugoslavia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cabot</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Belgrade</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-07-05T08:00:00+01:00"
                            >July 5, 1947—8 a. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>753. Despite what Bebler<note n="1" xml:id="d336fn1">Aleš Bebler, Yugoslav
                        Assistant Minister for Foreign Affairs.</note> told me Tuesday (<gloss
                        target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 734 July 1 repeated Rome 72<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d336fn2">Not printed; in it Cabot reported that: “Bebler informed me
                        today that Yugos would ratify Italian treaty this afternoon.” (740.0011 EW
                        (Peace)/6–147)</note>) I understand Italian Treaty has not yet been ratified
                    by Presidium. Reason given by Foreign Office is that ratification should first
                    be completed for Bulgarian and Hungarian treaties since these are now considered
                    friendly nations.</p>
                <p>Sent Department as 753, repeated Rome 78.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cabot</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
